### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
create a regex expression to extract a three character code like "1Jn" from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm".  The characters can be upper or lower case letters or digits. And the filename extension must be ".usfm".

### Response:


To create a regex expression to extract a three character code like "1Jn" from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm", you would use something along these lines:

RegExp = "^1Nj$ 20-1Nj$ 30-1Nj$ 40-1Nj$ 50-1Nj$"

The RegExp will match a three character code like "1Jn". The filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm" would have the same structure as ".usfm". This expression should capture any information in the specified structure.
